This paper is about optimizing the memory efficiency of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) on GPUs. The primary focus is on the performance implications of data layouts and memory access patterns for CNN layers. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), machine learning (cs.LG), and robotics (cs.AR).
